# Cron fallback for the overnight runner (Linux, or Mac if you prefer cron to launchd).
#
# The installer generates and installs the real line for you with your own paths.
# This is what it looks like — a job at 01:00 every day, pointed at your job file,
# with output logged so a failed run is never silent.
#
# Install by hand instead of via the installer:
#   ( crontab -l 2>/dev/null; cat crontab.example ) | crontab -
# Then edit the placeholder paths with `crontab -e`.
#
# NOTE: cron does NOT wake a sleeping machine. On a laptop that sleeps, prefer
# launchd (Mac) or Task Scheduler (Windows) — both can wake the machine. Use cron
# on an always-on box (a server, a Raspberry Pi, a machine that never sleeps).
#
# Fields:  min hour day month weekday   command
0 1 * * * /usr/bin/env python3 /ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/overnight_runner.py --job /ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/my-job.sh --minutes 45 >> "$HOME/.local/state/youragent-overnight/cron.log" 2>&1
